bottom:32px;"><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;In=
ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">One mystery in particular has captivated the le=
gal community
regarding Baldoni=E2=80=99s lawsuit: Why opt for a California state court? =
After all, not only is there an expansive state anti-SLAPP law that swiftly=
 dismisses meritless cases, it also awards legal costs=E2=80=94meaning Bald=
oni could be forced to pay the <em>Times</em>=E2=80=99s legal fees. Plus, t=
he <em>Times</em> can kick this to federal court and pursue an immediate ap=
peal if its anti-SLAPP bid fails. In other words, don=E2=80=99t expect a tr=
ial anytime soon.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p =
style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">When I contacted Freedman, he was unc=
haracteristically tight-lipped about his strategy. My guess? He=E2=80=99s m=
ore comfortable with the local legal arena, betting on the known quantities=
 on the bench.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">However, I do wonder if it has any=
thing to do with a notable ruling last year in former film financier <stron=
g>Ryan Kavanaugh</strong>=E2=80=99s case against podcaster <strong>Ethan
Klein</strong>, where a judge allowed a libel suit to proceed despite an an=
ti-SLAPP challenge centered on the application of fair report privilege. Th=
e dispute is terribly complicated=E2=80=94see <a href=3D"https://email.puck=
=2Enews/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1l=
EQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVUTRpRnltM0J6NjJNU3h3V=
Ws3Zz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvcnlhbi1rYXZhbmF1Z2hzLW1lZGlhLWxl=
Z2FsLXRocmlsbGVyLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249V2hhdCtJJTI3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0N=
SSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjclMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PVdoYXQrSSUyN20rSGVhcm=
luZyUyQistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkY3JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtY=
WlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2=
MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQ=
iOjIyMjkwM30/501543cf18ac1935106200455f2a4c045513134f0f2452daf66e9e1411f7ab=
62" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">my prior report</a> =
for details=E2=80=94but long story short: Klein failed in his attempt to in=
voke the shield because the judge didn=E2=80=99t think what he repeated abo=
ut Kavanaugh operating a =E2=80=9CPonzi scheme=E2=80=9D was
particularly <em>fair</em>. (Incidentally, California=E2=80=99s 2nd appella=
te division will hold a hearing on this matter on Wednesday, delving into r=
epublication liability and the almost metaphysical nature of what constitut=
es a =E2=80=9Cfiling=E2=80=9D for privilege purposes.)</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Maybe Freedman has=
 his eyes on a favorable precedent, or perhaps he likes his odds of setting=
 his own. He=E2=80=99ll surely be arguing that the <em>Times</em> overstepp=
ed by
coordinating with Lively=E2=80=99s team and taking their word about a filin=
g with the California Civil Rights Department. Either way, the Hollywood at=
torney might want to tread carefully. A lawyer who so regularly texts repor=
ters might not like how this one turns out.</p></div>
